---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Reading List — Yannik Peschke" 
  description="Books and reading recommendations about software engineering, architecture, and system design."
>

<h1>Reading List</h1>
<p class="page-intro">
  Books that shaped my thinking on software engineering, system design, and building better software. 
  These are recommendations for anyone interested in deepening their understanding of these topics.
</p>

<h2>Architecture & Design</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Building Microservices</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Sam Newman</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        The definitive guide to microservices architecture. Newman covers everything from identifying service 
        boundaries to deployment strategies, monitoring, and organizational impact. Essential reading for 
        understanding distributed systems.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Architecture</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Microservices</span>
        <span class="book-tag">System Design</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Domain-Driven Design</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Eric Evans</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        The classic text on DDD. While dense, it's invaluable for learning how to model complex domains and 
        establish a shared language between technical and business teams. The concepts of bounded contexts 
        and aggregates are fundamental to good architecture.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Architecture</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Domain Modeling</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Design Patterns</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Designing Data-Intensive Applications</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Martin Kleppmann</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        An incredible deep dive into the fundamentals of data systems. Covers databases, distributed systems, 
        consistency models, and how modern applications handle data at scale. Accessible yet thorough.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">System Design</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Databases</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Distributed Systems</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Software Architecture: The Hard Parts</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Neal Ford, Mark Richards, et al.</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Focuses on the difficult architectural decisions: where to split services, how to manage data ownership, 
        handling distributed transactions, and navigating trade-offs. Practical guidance for real-world challenges.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Architecture</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Decision Making</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Trade-offs</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Frontend & Web Development</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Micro Frontends in Action</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Michael Geers</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Practical guide to implementing microfrontends. Covers different integration techniques, team organization, 
        and real-world patterns. Great for understanding when microfrontends make sense and how to implement them 
        effectively.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Microfrontends</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Frontend</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Architecture</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>High Performance Browser Networking</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Ilya Grigorik</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Essential understanding of how the web actually works. From TCP/IP to HTTP/2, WebSockets, and performance 
        optimization. Knowing these fundamentals makes you a better frontend engineer.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Performance</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Networking</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Web</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Software Craft</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>The Pragmatic Programmer</h3>
      <p class="book-author">David Thomas, Andrew Hunt</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Timeless advice on being a better software developer. Covers everything from code organization to career 
        development. The 20th anniversary edition has been updated but the core principles remain relevant.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Best Practices</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Career</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Fundamentals</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>A Philosophy of Software Design</h3>
      <p class="book-author">John Ousterhout</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Short but impactful book about managing complexity in software. Ousterhout's ideas about deep modules, 
        information hiding, and when abstraction helps versus hurts are incredibly valuable. Changed how I think 
        about API design.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Design</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Complexity</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Philosophy</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Working Effectively with Legacy Code</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Michael Feathers</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Most developers spend more time maintaining existing systems than building new ones. This book provides 
        strategies for safely refactoring and improving code you didn't write. Practical techniques for breaking 
        dependencies and adding tests.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Refactoring</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Testing</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Maintenance</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Organization & Process</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Team Topologies</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Matthew Skelton, Manuel Pais</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        How you organize teams impacts your architecture and vice versa. This book provides patterns for 
        structuring teams to optimize for fast flow and clear ownership. Essential for understanding the 
        organizational side of technical decisions.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Organization</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Teams</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Architecture</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-cover">BOOK</div>
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Accelerate</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Nicole Forsgren, Jez Humble, Gene Kim</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Data-driven insights into what makes high-performing technology organizations. Based on years of research, 
        it identifies the key capabilities that drive software delivery performance. Backs up best practices with 
        research.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">DevOps</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Performance</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Research</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</Layout>

<style>
.page-intro {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
}

h2 {
  margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

h2:first-of-type {
  margin-top: 0;
}

.book-list {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-lg);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
}

.book-item {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 100px 1fr;
  gap: var(--spacing-md);
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  background: transparent;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.book-item:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
  padding-left: calc(var(--spacing-lg) + 10px);
}

.book-item:last-child {
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.book-item:last-child:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
}

.book-cover {
  width: 100px;
  height: 150px;
  background-color: transparent;
  border: 1px dashed var(--border-color);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.book-info h3 {
  font-size: 1.375rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.book-info h3::before {
  content: ">";
  margin-right: 10px;
  color: var(--accent);
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateX(-10px);
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.book-item:hover .book-info h3::before {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateX(0);
}

.book-item:hover .book-info h3 {
  color: var(--accent);
}

.book-author {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: 14px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.book-description {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
}

.book-tags {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--spacing-xs);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.book-tag {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: 11px;
  padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .book-item {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .book-cover {
    width: 100%;
    height: 80px;
  }
}
</style>
